WEBVTT

00:34.159 --> 00:36.326
In the
spring of 1946,

00:36.411 --> 00:38.787
in the small town
of Texarkana,

00:38.872 --> 00:40.998
on the
Texas-Arkansas border,

00:41.082 --> 00:43.667
a series of horrific murders
were committed

00:43.752 --> 00:47.755
by a masked assailant
known only as
"The Phantom Killer."

00:48.757 --> 00:50.507
For three harrowing months,

00:50.592 --> 00:53.802
the Phantom stalked the
back roads of Texarkana,

00:53.887 --> 00:57.848
following young couples
looking for privacy to
isolated areas,

00:57.932 --> 01:01.685
where their screams
for help would go
unanswered.

01:01.770 --> 01:05.689
Though several arrests
were made in connection
with the brutal slayings,

01:05.774 --> 01:08.025
which ended as suddenly
as they began,

01:08.109 --> 01:11.361
the killer's identity
was never confirmed.

01:11.446 --> 01:14.782
Indeed, many people
who lived through
that nightmare time

01:14.866 --> 01:18.619
believed the Phantom spent
the rest of his days free,

01:18.703 --> 01:20.704
walking the streets
of Texarkana

01:20.789 --> 01:25.375
quietly, anonymously,
until his assumed death.

01:25.460 --> 01:28.837
In 1976, a film inspired
by the infamous

01:28.922 --> 01:31.632
Moonlight Murders
was released.

01:31.716 --> 01:34.885
Every year, on Halloween,
The Town That
Dreaded Sundown

01:34.969 --> 01:38.639
is screened somewhere
in Texarkana,

01:38.723 --> 01:43.894
in tribute to the Phantom's
legacy of death and blood.

01:43.978 --> 01:47.689
Today, Texarkana is a place
haunted by its past,

01:47.774 --> 01:50.818
defined by a mystery
that was never solved,

01:50.902 --> 01:54.238
and a tragedy that
could never be forgotten.

01:54.322 --> 01:58.742
The following happened
in Texarkana last year.

02:20.473 --> 02:23.433
Sammy! Sammy!

02:27.188 --> 02:29.189
You're not enjoying
this, are you?

02:31.025 --> 02:33.527
Oh, I just don't like
these kinds of films
so much.

02:34.487 --> 02:36.864
Why didn't you say so?

02:37.657 --> 02:38.657
We can go.

02:39.701 --> 02:41.952
Really? Do you mean it?

02:47.375 --> 02:48.709
